        <h2 id= "Ham">Ham Sandwich</h2>
        
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/ff/Mmm...hot_ham_and_cheese_with_homemade_mustard_%284970848133%29.jpg/800px-Mmm...hot_ham_and_cheese_with_homemade_mustard_%284970848133%29.jpg" alt="Ham sanwich" width="200">
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 5 minutes</li>
            <li>Serves:1 person</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Bread, Ham, cheese.
                    <td> 2 slices of any bread, 2 slices of Ham, 1 slice of any cheese. 
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Take out 2 slices of Bread.
        <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Place 2 slices of Ham onto the Bread </p>
</p>
<p><strong>Step 3:</strong>Then place one slice of cheese on either side of the Bread</p>

<h2 id="hotd">Hot dog</h2>
<img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b1/Hot_dog_with_mustard.png/1024px-Hot_dog_with_mustard.png" alt="Hot dog" width="200">
   <ul>
    <li>Time: 15 minutes</li>
    <li>Serves: 1 person</li>
    
   </ul>
   <table>
       <thead>
           <tr>
               <th>Ingredients</th>
               <th>Quantity</th>
           </tr>
           <tr>
               <td>Hot dog bun, Beef Hot dog</td>
               <td>1 hot dog bun, 1 beef hot dog
           </tr>
       </thead>
   </table>
   
   <p><strong>Step 1:</strong>Turn on stove and place a pan on top.</p>
   <p><strong>Step 2:</strong>Place oil or butter within pan, and let heat up</p>
   <p><strong>Step 3:</strong>Place the hotdog into the pan once at proper heat</p>
   <p><strong>Step 4:</strong>Cook hotdog on one side for 4 to 5 minutes, then flip onto other side and let cook for 4 to 5 minutes</p>
   <p><strong>Step 5:</strong>Take out hotdog bun and <strong>with tongs</strong> take out hotdog and place within bun</p>
   
   <h2 id="sal">Salad</h2>
   <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Salad_platter.jpg/800px-Salad_platter.jpg" alt="Salad" width="200">
   
   <ul>
       <li>Time: 5 minutes</li>
       <li>Serves: 4 people</li>
   </ul>
   
   <table>
       <thead>
       <tr>
           <th>Ingredients</th>
           <th>Quantity</th>
       </tr>
       <tr>
           <td> Lettuce, tomatoe, any Dressing</td>
           <td> A head of Lettuce, 1 tomatoe, a bottle of dressing
       </tr>
       </thead>
   </table>
   <p><strong>Step 1:</strong>Take out the head of Lettuce and <strong><em>carefully</em></strong> slice thinly.</p>
   <p><strong>Step 2:</strong>Then take the Tomatoe and also cut it carefully</p>
   <p><strong>Step 3:</strong>Then place the cut up Lettuce and Tomatoe into a bowl, and drizzle dressing of choice within the bowl</p>
   <p><strong>Step 4:</strong>Finally, toss salad with tongs and serve.</P>
    <p><em>Source: <a href="https://www.wikihow.com/Cook-Hot-Dogs#Grilling-Hot-Dogs">Some recipes websites</a></em></p>
    
